HEADWORD: Soothsayer
<hw>Sooth"say`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who foretells events by the art of soothsaying; a
prognosticator.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A mantis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soothsaying</ent>⟦br⟧
